// Job catalog. Each Workstation entity in the world references one of these
// specs by ID (Workstation.specId). Tweaking values here is the primary lever
// for gameplay-economy balance — wages, skill XP rates, shift hours, and
// hiring requirements all live in this file.
//
// Field guide:
//   jobTitle:       short display title shown in NPC labels and the StatusPanel
//   wage:           money awarded per shift completed at 100% perf (scales by
//                   wageMultiplier(perf) and the worker's job-relevant attribute)
//   skillXp:        skill XP awarded per perfect shift (0 = no skill XP at all)
//   skill:          which skill receives the XP, or null when skillXp is 0
//   shiftStart:     hour-of-day the shift opens (0–23, or 24 to mean "midnight")
//   shiftEnd:       hour-of-day the shift closes; values up to 24 cover the
//                   wraparound (e.g., 18..24 = evening; 0..12 = morning)
//   workDays:       day-of-week numbers the shift runs on; 0=Sun, 6=Sat
//   requirements:   minimum skill levels needed to be hired (entries omitted
//                   when there are no requirements)
//   description:    HR-listing blurb shown to the player
//   playerHireable: false marks an NPC-only role; HRConversation hides these from
//                   the player's listing while NPCs can still claim them
//   installOnly:    true marks a seat NPCs must never auto-claim through the BT
//                   find-job path — only the player's install dialog (secretary,
//                   recruiter) can seat someone. Faction-misc convenience seats
//                   are meaningless without a player owner.
{
  catalog: {
    factory_engineer: {
      jobTitle: '工程师',
      wage: 190,
      skillXp: 100,
      skill: 'mechanics',
      shiftStart: 9,
      shiftEnd: 17,
      workDays: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5],     // Mon–Fri
      requirements: { mechanics: 30, computers: 5 },
      description: '设计与开发任务。',
      playerHireable: true,
    },

